          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                                        <date>March 1./54</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Friend—</p>
                              <p>Hardly anything of any interest<lb/> has transpired since my
                                        last<lb/> Letter, which might serve You as a<lb/> Matter of
                                        News; however I will drop<lb/> a few Lines to you, to inform
                                        you of<lb/> a Ball to be given by the “Hebrew<lb/>
                                        Benevolent Society,” on next “<date>Purim</date>”<lb/> which
                                        promises so far to be a fine<lb/> affair; a large number of
                                        tickets<lb/> have already been disposed, and the<lb/>
                                        managers make active preparations<lb/> to get up a Ball
                                                  <sic>praiseworty</sic> of the<lb/> society; the
                                        tickets are sold at $10. The Emani El Congregation<lb/> had
                                        drawn several plans for a<lb/> synagogue, &amp; have chosen
                                        one, &amp; are now<lb/> about giving out proposals; the plan
                                        prescribes<lb/> the Gothic style, &amp; when finished will
                                        be<lb/> one of the finest synagogues in the
                                                  <placeName>United<lb/> States</placeName>; the
                                        Building will be about 50 x 80 feet.<lb/> “Mazos” will be
                                        sold at 22¢ pr. pound<lb/> The baking of it will shortly be
                                        begun.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p><persName>Mr. &amp; Mrs. Roggenburger</persName> give their
                                        best<lb/> Respects to you; &amp; Hoping this will find<lb/>
                                        you in good spirits &amp; Health</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I remain yours Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <persName role="author">Cauffman H. Meyer</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>P.S. You will have recd a Letter from the<lb/> sec. of the Em.
                                        congregation about a chason &amp;<lb/> the advertisement</p>
